terms.description:
Report artifacts are the files already sitting in report storage after computation.

Examples:
1) a live current-prediction report;
2) a [[developer-home-backfilled-history|backfilled history]] report for a past date;
3) a backtest summary;
4) policy_branch_mega, PFI, and model-stats snapshots.

What it shows:
Those are the files the API project `SolSignalModel1D_Backtest.Api` reads and serves to the frontend.

How to read it:
If a screen is empty, first check whether the required file exists in storage, then check its contract. The full storage and API flow is described on the reports and API page.
